cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with image retrieval, which is a computer vision task, and specifically focuses on the Bag-of-Words (BoW) model. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia), and the use of probabilistic frameworks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with indexing structures, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and the problem of false matches, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
